Two men were yesterday arraigned and charged with obstructing police officers and being in possession of bhang. Steven Gikonyo and Antony Kariuki were accused of obstructing officers Keith Robert, Bethwel Kibet and Kenneth Mworia on September 12 while the officers were executing their duties. The court was also told that the accused were arrested for being in possession of 20 rolls of bhang and refusing to be detained by the officers.